An auctioneer on Monday denied conning a businessman out of Sh1 million.Kevin Mutahi, 30, allegedly defrauded David Githua by lying that he was in a position to procure seeds from Uganda that help in cancer treatment.Police say the crime took place between March 9 and June 9 last year at Githua&rsquo;s Kengeles restaurant.Mutahi is the director of Kevco Enterprises Auctioneers.He was also charged with five counts of issuing a bad cheque to Githua for Sh1.3 million.Kibera senior principal magistrate Elizabeth Juma released him on Sh1 million bond with a similar surety or Sh1 million bail.The hearing was set for May 15.